After completing this course, students will be able to :

- understand the ecology (education, creation, promotion, conservation, creative cultural industries, cultural entrepreneurship) for art development of Hong Kong and its ultimate goals for development quality life and civil society;
- understand the significance of different roles (artist, curator, administrator, critics, educationist, researchers, promoters, audience) in helping to shape the art ecology;
- understand the nature of art organizations/government/corporates/creative industries and their importance in helping to support the development of the art ecology; and

- see the possibilities for themselves career-wise and for contributing to art development within and without Hong Kong.

After completing the course, students will be able to:

1. understand their personal strength by developing short term research on individual topics;
2. build and polish their technique and presentation skill in art, thus develop a professional attitude;
3. understand issues of contemporary art and develop individual reflections; and

4. develop and broaden their critical thinking skills through different perspectives through the system of visiting artists/ critics

